</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF846A3BFA5891BF17E2B335" box="[1444,2530,2022,2055]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF846A3BFA5891BF17E2B335" blockId="127.[1442,2650,1433,2607]" box="[1444,2530,2022,2055]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF846A3BFA5891BF18A9B335" bold="true" box="[1444,1705,2022,2055]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
The Nut-colored Yellow Bat apparently forages over water.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF846A3BFA589E541863B364" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="breeding">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF846A3BFA589E541863B364" blockId="127.[1442,2650,1433,2607]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF846A3BFA589E54182AB31C" bold="true" box="[1444,1578,2061,2094]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Breeding.</emphasis>
Two Nut-colored Yellow Bats with one fetus each were recorded in March in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF846A3BFA359E6C1860B364" box="[1481,1632,2101,2134]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF846A3BFA5E9E051862B2A0" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="activity">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF846A3BFA5E9E051862B2A0" blockId="127.[1442,2650,1433,2607]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF846A3BFA5E9E05188CB34F" bold="true" box="[1442,1676,2140,2173]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Nut-colored Yellow Bat roosts in hollow trees and in small groups in roofs of houses. In western 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF846A3BF89D9EDA19D1B396" box="[1889,2001,2179,2212]" name="Uganda" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, echolocation calls had minimum frequency of 40-7 kHz, maximum frequency of 54-1 kHz, characteristic frequency of 43 kHz, frequency of the knee of 45-1 kHz, and duration of 2 milliseconds. In 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF846A3BF6649E8317F8B3C1" box="[2456,2552,2266,2291]" name="Gabon" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Gabon</collectingCountry>
, mean minimum frequency was 38-5 kHz (37-8-40), mean maximum frequency was 59-5 kHz (52-5-75-8), mean dominant frequency was 44-5 kHz (41:1-47-4), mean duration was 1-9 milliseconds (1-6-2-5), and mean interpulse interval was 57-1 milliseconds (16-2-108-6).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF846A3BFA599FCE1751B28A" box="[1445,2385,2455,2488]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF846A3BFA599FCE1751B28A" blockId="127.[1442,2650,1433,2607]" box="[1445,2385,2455,2488]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF846A3BFA599FCE1662B28A" bold="true" box="[1445,2146,2455,2488]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF846A3BFA5A9FE717C0B2ED" box="[1446,2496,2494,2527]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF846A3BFA5A9FE717C0B2ED" blockId="127.[1442,2650,1433,2607]" box="[1446,2496,2494,2527]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF846A3BFA5A9FE71903B2ED" bold="true" box="[1446,1795,2494,2527]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red Lust.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
